50|$|After {{working at}} the Duke of Baden Brewery of the Black Forest region in Baden, Germany, Francis Xavier Matt I immigrated to the United States in 1880. Matt worked at the <b>Charles</b> <b>Bierbauer</b> Brewery as lead {{salesman}} and brewmaster in Utica {{for a few years}} before reorganizing it into The West End Brewing Company in 1888.|$|E
5000|$|Francis Xavier Matt {{acquired}} his brewing expertise as {{a student}} of the Duke of Baden, and was considered a proficient brewer upon his arrival in the city of Utica in 1880. His grandson, F.X. Matt II, remarked that, under the duke's tutelage, F.X. Matt I gained brewing experience [...] "as an art, not a science; as a way of life, not a way of making a living." [...] Combining his talents with <b>Charles</b> <b>Bierbauer,</b> who was additionally skillful in old world brewing techniques, Matt nurtured a reputation in Utica's westside that resulted in his role as brewmaster, superintendent, and treasurer of a newly organized West End Brewing Company in 1888. F.X. Matt led the brewery until 1951.|$|E

